data.title: Altamont x Erin M. Riley Collaboration
data.description:
Altamont is proud to introduce our newest collaboration with Erin M. Riley.

Erin M. Riley lives and works in Brooklyn, NY, but grew up in Cape Cod. She’s spent years working in her studio, while traveling in her pickup truck hosting artist residencies throughout the country.

Being a woman inspires her work, through her teen years in chat rooms, as well as modern day digital imagery through the lens of her computer and phone cameras. Erin’s spent her recent years pursuing images people share, adding her own, and uses wool on a loom to present her own personal art from it.

Each piece presents a confrontation as it stares down the dull as well as peers into the minds and souls of the close-minded pawns.

data.title: Altamont Presents Andrew Reynolds “Polaroids”
data.description:
Though he’s never pursued any kind of recognition for his photography, Andrew Reynolds has been consistently shooting pictures since his early days in Florida. Residing in shoe boxes at his house are thousands of polaroids and 35mm prints: Childhood images from the 80s, snapshots from Birdhouse tours, hang-overs from the Warner Ave Piss Drunx days, and shots taken of everybody that stopped by Drew’s house in the last few years.

This collection, curated by Patrick O' Dell, was shown for the first time at KNOWN Gallery in Los Angeles on May 14th, 2014.
